OL,3,COlympic star fears Chinese swimmers'
OL,4,Cfailed drugs tests risk 'tarnishing'
OL,5,Csport
OL,7,FThe World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA)
OL,8,Fhad accepted the explanation of
OL,9,Fauthorities in China that the swimmers
OL,10,Fhad unknowingly consumed food
OL,11,Fcontaminated with trimetazidine, a
OL,12,Fpotent heart drug, during a training
OL,13,Fcamp held months before the 2021
OL,14,FOlympics in Tokyo.
OL,16,FThe boss of the US Anti-Doping Agency
OL,17,Faccused WADA of having "swept these
OL,18,Fpositives under the carpet," something
OL,19,Fthe global authority described as
OL,20,F"outrageous, completely false and
OL,21,Fdefamatory."
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/7
